From: Steev Klimaszewski <threeway@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 18:37:52 -0600
Subject: arm64: qcom_laptops.config: Enable UHID

Some modern bluetooth mice require UHID in order to work properly.
Enable it as a module.

Signed-off-by: Steev Klimaszewski <threeway@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
index f165180c8132..b301b1373234 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
@@ -99,3 +99,4 @@ CONFIG_SND_USB_AUDIO_MIDI_V2=y
 CONFIG_FW_LOADER_COMPRESS=y
 CONFIG_FW_LOADER_COMPRESS_XZ=y
 CONFIG_FW_LOADER_COMPRESS_ZSTD=y
+CONFIG_UHID
-- 
2.53.0

